defaultRecog
defaultnition and reward for non-research activities
default1
default3
default. Another challenge within academia is that 
defaultnon-research 
defaultskills 
default(e.g. leadership, mentoring, 
defaultpastoral care
default, teaching, project/lab management
default)
default appear to be largely ignored when it comes to advancing up the pyramid. Considering the impact sponsorship by a senior scientist can have on a rising career, it is worrying that the presence of this support is largely left to chance rather than being embe
defaultdded into academic culture. We feel that weighting promotions on the basis of wider skills (
defaultand including 
default‘360-degree feedback’) once research calibre has been established would help reward those who contribute to a supportive work culture.
default1
default4
default. This also t
defaultouches on observations our members have made about the type of additional work taken on by women in STEM. It is widely known
default,
